@startuml
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam backgroundColor #fcfcfd
skinparam defaultFontName Helvetica
skinparam defaultFontSize 14
skinparam arrowColor #0f172a
skinparam noteBackgroundColor #fff7d6
skinparam noteBorderColor #b45309
skinparam noteFontColor #334155
skinparam roundcorner 16
title State Machine - gdp/GdpPipeline
skinparam state {
  backgroundColor #f8fafc
  borderColor #0f172a
  fontColor #0f172a
  startColor #1d4ed8
  endColor #0f172a
}
left to right direction
hide empty description
state "Observe" as observe
state "EvaluateReady" as evaluate_ready
state "Ready" as ready
state "Retryable" as retryable
state "Failed" as failed
observe : read spec, tracked status, delete intent,\nand current OCI lifecycle
state "ResolveByLookup" as resolve_by_lookup
state "RejectUnsupportedDrift" as reject_unsupported_drift
state "ApplyUpdate" as apply_update
state "DeletePending" as delete_pending
state "Deleted" as deleted
state "DeleteCleanupBlocked" as delete_cleanup_blocked
[*] --> observe : CreateGdpPipeline
observe --> resolve_by_lookup : tracked identity missing
resolve_by_lookup --> evaluate_ready : lookup or create reaches\nACTIVE, INACTIVE
resolve_by_lookup --> retryable : OCI state in CREATING,\nUPDATING, DELETING
resolve_by_lookup --> failed : unresolved OCI error or non-success state
observe --> evaluate_ready : OCI state in ACTIVE,\nINACTIVE
observe --> retryable : OCI state in CREATING,\nUPDATING, DELETING
observe --> failed : unresolved OCI error or non-success state
evaluate_ready --> reject_unsupported_drift : force-new or conflicting\ndrift detected
reject_unsupported_drift --> ready : wait for spec or live state change
evaluate_ready --> apply_update : supported mutable drift for\napproval_key_vault_id,\nauthorization_details,\ndefined_tags (+9 more)
apply_update --> ready : update path completes
evaluate_ready --> ready : no supported drift remains
ready --> ready : no supported drift remains
retryable --> retryable : OCI remains retryable
failed --> failed : OCI remains terminal
ready --> delete_pending : delete requested
retryable --> delete_pending : delete requested
failed --> delete_pending : delete requested
delete_pending --> delete_cleanup_blocked : cleanup or finalizer release remains blocked
delete_cleanup_blocked --> deleted : retry delete completion until allowed
deleted --> deleted : terminal stutter
note right of ready
shared diagram:
shared/diagrams/shared-controller-state-machine.svg
Start from the shared controller phase model and
specialize imported provider states, delete
targets, and failure exits here.
archetype batch: Generated service-manager
controllers map provider states into the shared
controller phases with explicit finalizer and
requeue policies.
service: gdp
slug: gdppipeline
kind: GdpPipeline
archetype: generated-service-manager
status/finalizer: required /
retain-until-confirmed-delete
requeue: provisioning, updating, terminating
provider states: create CREATING, UPDATING;
update UPDATING; delete DELETING
supported drift: approval_key_vault_id,
authorization_details, defined_tags, description
(+8 more)
reject before mutate: force-new fields
bucket_details, compartment_id, peering_region,
pipeline_type
create-only fields: none
list lookup: oci_gdp_gdp_pipelines filters
compartment_id, display_name, gdp_pipeline_id,
lifecycle_state
conflicts: none
open gaps: none
GdpPipeline create, update, and delete are
work-request-backed. The runtime records the
opening opc-work-request-id, polls
GetGdpWorkRequest through the generatedruntime
async seam, and rereads GetGdpPipeline before
projecting status or completing delete
confirmation.
GDP work-request OperationStatus values
normalize into the shared async classes and GDP
operation types normalize into create, update,
and delete phases. Raw work-request status,
operation type, message, percent complete, and
work-request ID remain visible in
status.async.current for debugging.
Success states are explicit: ACTIVE and INACTIVE
settle success, while NEEDS_ATTENTION is
terminal non-success rather than a default
active state.
Pre-create reuse is exact on compartmentId,
displayName, pipelineType, and peeringRegion,
and the runtime confirms bucketDetails from a
follow-up GET before binding to an existing
pipeline. When a tracked OCID already exists,
list reuse stays keyed to the service-specific
gdpPipelineId filter.
Mutable drift is limited to
UpdateGdpPipelineDetails fields displayName,
description, serviceLogGroupId, fileTypes,
authorizationDetails,
isFileOverrideInDestinationEnabled,
isScanningEnabled, isChunkingEnabled,
isApprovalNeeded, approvalKeyVaultId,
freeformTags, and definedTags. Strings, maps,
and false booleans keep explicit clear intent,
while zero-length fileTypes clears remain
unpublished because the pinned SDK update
request omits empty slices.
Start/Stop/Peer/Rotate/ChangeCompartment
auxiliaries remain out-of-scope drift for the
published contract.
end note
note right of delete_pending
delete policy: required
delete observe: GetGdpPipeline or
ListGdpPipelines
delete targets: DELETED
end note
@enduml
